# Styling — shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS 3

## Stack

- **shadcn/ui** primitives in `web/src/components/ui/`
- **Tailwind CSS 3** with `@tailwind` directives in `web/src/styles.css`
- **Lucide React** for icons — no inline SVGs
- **`cn()`** from `web/src/lib/utils.ts` for conditional classes

## Design Tokens (CSS variables)

```css
--background: 0 0 0;
--foreground: 255 255 255;
--card: 17 17 17;
--primary: 139 92 246;
--accent: 34 197 94;
--muted: 39 39 42;
--destructive: 239 68 68;
--border: 39 39 42;
--radius: 0.75rem;
```

## Usage

```typescript
import { cn } from '../../lib/utils';
import { Button } from '../ui/button';

<div className={cn('rounded-lg bg-card text-foreground', isActive && 'ring-2 ring-primary')}>
  <Button variant="outline" size="sm">Action</Button>
</div>
```

## Rules

- ❌ NEVER use MUI — this project has no MUI dependency
- ❌ NEVER use arbitrary hex colors when a token exists
- ✅ USE shadcn/ui components (`Button`, `Card`, `Dialog`, etc.)
- ✅ USE Lucide icons: `import { FileText } from 'lucide-react'`
- ✅ USE `cn()` for conditional Tailwind classes
- Button variants: `default`, `destructive`, `outline`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `link`
- Write accessible markup with proper ARIA labels

See [docs/architecture/components-layer.md](../../docs/architecture/components-layer.md).
